Privacy Policy
BIST Maliyet Asistanı (BIST Cost & Profit Calculator)

Effective date: July 17, 2026

This Privacy Policy explains how Seher Aydin ("we", "us", or "our") handles information in connection with the BIST Maliyet Asistanı mobile application (the "App"). We are committed to protecting your privacy. Please read this policy carefully.

By using the App, you agree to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.

1. Information We Collect
Information you enter in the App. The App lets you enter data such as stock prices, quantities, dates, and record names to calculate costs, profit/loss, and dividends. This data is stored only on your device. We do not collect it, transmit it to our servers, or have any access to it.

Information collected automatically by advertising. The App displays banner advertisements through Google AdMob. To serve and measure ads, Google may collect certain information automatically, including device identifiers (such as an advertising ID), IP address, approximate (non-precise) location, device and operating system details, and information about your interaction with ads.

We ourselves do not collect, store, or process any of this advertising data — it is handled by Google.

1. We Do Not Require an Account
The App does not require registration or a login. We do not ask for your name, email address, phone number, or any other personal identifier in order to use the App.

1. How Your Data Is Stored
All calculations and records you create are saved locally on your device using your device's standard local storage. This data stays on your device and is removed when you delete the records within the App or uninstall the App.

1. Import and Export
The App allows you to import and export your calculation data as files that you choose. These files are handled locally on your device and are not sent to us. You are solely responsible for any file you choose to share or store outside the App.

1. Third-Party Services
The App uses the following third-party services, which have their own privacy policies:

Google AdMob (advertising) — https://policies.google.com/privacy
Google Play Services / Apple App Store (for app updates and delivery) — subject to Google's and Apple's respective privacy policies.
We encourage you to review these policies to understand how these providers handle data.

1. Advertising and Your Choices
Ads shown in the App may be personalized based on the advertising identifier on your device. You can limit or reset ad personalization at any time through your device settings:

iOS: Settings → Privacy & Security → Tracking / Apple Advertising
Android: Settings → Privacy → Ads (reset or delete advertising ID)
1. Data Sharing and Selling
We do not sell your personal information. We do not share your data with third parties, except for the advertising and platform services described above, which operate under their own privacy policies.

1. Data Retention and Deletion
Because your calculation data is stored only on your device, we do not retain it. You can delete your data at any time by removing records in the App or by uninstalling the App. Data processed by Google AdMob is retained according to Google's policies.

1. Children's Privacy
The App is not directed to children under the age of 13 (or the minimum age required in your country). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided personal information, please contact us so we can take appropriate action.

1. Security
We take reasonable measures to protect information handled by the App. However, no method of electronic storage or transmission is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

1. Your Rights
Depending on your location, you may have rights regarding your personal data, such as the right to access, correct, or delete it. Since we do not collect or store your personal data on our servers, most such requests should be directed to the third-party services listed above. For any questions, you may contact us using the details below.

1. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected by updating the "Effective date" at the top of this policy. Continued use of the App after changes take effect constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
